        "title": "How to resolve a &quot;Null manifest from input stream associated with&quot; warning",
        "body": "<p>I'm trying to stop the warning: <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>JarClassLoader: Warning: Null manifest from input stream associated with: &lt;path to lib / jar file&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>which gets displayed every time I run my java application. I realise that it doesn't stop it working, but I assume a warning is there for a reason and I'd like to understand why and how.<\/p>\n\n<p>For reference, the jar file is being created using one-jar.\nI've looked at this <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/3662659/one-jar-remove-verbose-warning-information-on-application-load\">stackoverflow question/answer<\/a> but this seems to be more about suppressing messages rather than resolving them. <\/p>\n\n<p>It also has been asked <a href=\"http://sourceforge.net/tracker/index.php?func=detail&amp;aid=3139182&amp;group_id=111153&amp;atid=658458\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">here<\/a> but again I couldn't find an answer.<\/p>\n",
